{
  "title": "QSS Webhooks",
  "keywords": "zoom, marketplace, webhook, event, create, update, delete, real-time, data, summary, qos, quality, service",
  "description": "[Zoom Quality of Service Subscription (QSS)](https://explore.zoom.us/en/qss/) is an add-on product that enables Developers to receive details about the network traffic in near real-time for users, hosts, and participants in their meetings, webinars, and phone calls. This data can be used to proactively troubleshoot and identify issues as quickly as possible. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) to add this feature.\n\n **Requirements**\n\n In addition to having the QSS product on your account, at least one user on the account must have Developer permissions enabled to be able to create an application that can subscribe to QSS events. This user should create a Zoom app to receive notifications.\n\n **Enabling QSS event notifications**\n\n On the Feature page for the Marketplace app, enable **Event Subscription** and add the **Event notification endpoint URL** to send the webhooks. Click **Add events** and select **QSS**. Select the QSS events that you\u2019d like to receive.\n\n Note that you must subscribe to the QSS summary event to receive data from the QoS summary APIs.",
  "skipQualtrics": true
}

    "meeting.participant_qos": {

        "operationId": "meeting.participant_qos",
        "requestBody": {
          "description": "# meeting.participant_qos\n\nWhen participants are in a meeting, the **Meeting Participant QoS** event collects performance data every 6 seconds, aggregates approximately 10 data points into one record every minute, and sends it.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for more information.\n* **Event Subscriptions** must be enabled for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build) with the following configurations:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Meeting Participant QoS** subscription enabled under the **QSS** event.\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard_meetings:read:admin`,`dashboard:read:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard:read:meeting_participant_qos:master`,`dashboard:read:meeting_participant_qos:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `meeting.participant_qos`\n",

              "schema": {
                "required": [
                  "event",
                  "event_ts",
                  "payload"

                    "description": "The name of the event."
                  },

                    "type": "integer",
                    "format": "int64",

                      "object"

                        "description": "The meeting host's account ID."
                      },

                        "description": "Information about the meeting.",

                          "uuid",
                          "participant"
                        ],

                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The meeting's universally unique identifier (UUID). Each meeting instance generates a meeting UUID."
                          },

                            "type": "object",
                            "description": "Information about the meeting participant.",
                            "required": [
                              "user_id",
                              "qos"
                            ],

                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The participant's meeting user ID. This value is assigned to a participant upon joining a meeting and is only valid for the duration of the meeting."

                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The participant's universally unique identifier (UUID). Returns an empty value for external users."

If the participant is not part of the host's account, this returns an empty string value, with some exceptions.                                           "enum": [

                                            "fair",
                                            "serious",
                                            "critical"
                                          ]
                                        },
                                        "quality": {

                                          "enum": [

                                            "fair",
                                            "good",

These levels are rough estimates of CPU usage: normal (~20%), fair (~50%), serious (~80%), and critical (~100%).",

                                            "description": "Unit of the wireless network's received signal strength indicator (RSSI).",
                                            "example": "dBm"

    "webinar.participant_qos": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "webinar"
        ],
        "operationId": "webinar.participant_qos",
        "requestBody": {
          "description": "# webinar.participant_qos\n\nWhen participants are in a webinar, the **Webinar Participant QoS** event collects performance metrics every 6 seconds. Zoom aggregates roughly 10 data into a single record every minute, then sends it to your endpoint.\n\n## Prerequisites\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for details.\n* **Event Subscriptions** must be enabled for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build), including:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Webinar Participant QoS** event enabled under the **QSS** event category.\n\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard_webinars:read:admin`,`dashboard:read:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard:read:webinar_participant_qos:master`,`dashboard:read:webinar_participant_qos:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `webinar.participant_qos`\n",
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "required": [
                  "event",
                  "event_ts",
                  "payload"
                ],
                "properties": {
                  "event": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "description": "The event's name."
                  },
                  "event_ts": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "format": "int64",
                    "description": "Timestamp in milliseconds since epoch when the event occurred. The value is returned in long (int64) format."
                  },
                  "payload": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "required": [
                      "account_id",
                      "object"
                    ],
                    "properties": {
                      "account_id": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "The Account ID associated with the event."
                      },
                      "object": {
                        "type": "object",
                        "description": "Meeting object.",
                        "required": [
                          "uuid",
                          "participant"
                        ],
                        "properties": {
                          "uuid": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The meeting's universally unique identifier (UUID)."
                          },
                          "participant": {
                            "type": "object",
                            "description": "Participant object.",
                            "required": [
                              "user_id",
                              "qos"
                            ],
                            "properties": {
                              "user_id": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The participant's unique identifier."
                              },
                              "participant_user_id": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The participant's universally unique identifier (UUID). Returns an empty value for external users."
                              },
                              "email": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "format": "email",
                                "description": "The participant's email address. This response only returns a value if the participant joined the meeting by logging into Zoom. If the participant is not part of the host's account, this returns an empty string value, with some exceptions. See [Email address display rules](/docs/api/using-zoom-apis/#email-address-display-rules) for details."
                              },
                              "qos": {
                                "type": "array",
                                "description": "An array of Quality of Service (QoS) data.",
                                "items": {
                                  "type": "object",
                                  "description": "Quality of Service (QoS) items.",
                                  "required": [
                                    "date_time",
                                    "type",
                                    "details"
                                  ],
                                  "properties": {
                                    "date_time": {
                                      "type": "string",
                                      "description": "The timestamp for when the participant left."
                                    },
                                    "type": {
                                      "type": "string",
                                      "description": "Quality of Service (QoS) type.",
                                      "enum": [
                                        "audio_input",
                                        "audio_output",
                                        "video_input",
                                        "video_output",
                                        "as_input",
                                        "as_output",
                                        "cpu_usage",

          "description": "# webinar.participant_qos_summary\n\nThe **Webinar Participant QoS Summary** event triggers each time a participant leaves a webinar. The collected QoS metrics for that participant are then sent via this event.\n\n## Prerequisites\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for details.\n* **Event Subscriptions** must be enabled for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build), including:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Webinar Participant QoS Summary** event enabled under the **QSS** event category.\n\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard_webinars:read:admin`,`dashboard:read:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard:read:webinar_participant_qos:master`,`dashboard:read:webinar_participant_qos:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `webinar.participant_qos_summary`\n",

        "requestBody": {
          "description": "# meeting.participant_data\n\nThe **Meeting Participant Data** event triggers when participants in a meeting make setting changes. For example, when a participant enables their camera, there will be an event notification triggered during the meeting. When you subscribe to this event, you will receive multiple events in one meeting for each participant.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for more information.\n* **Event Subscriptions** must be enabled for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build) with the following configurations:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Meeting Participant Data** subscription enabled under the **QSS** event.\n\n\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard_meetings:read:admin`,`dashboard:read:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `qss:read:meeting_participant_data:master`,`qss:read:meeting_participant_data:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `meeting.participant_data`\n",

            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "required": [
                  "event",
                  "event_ts",
                  "payload"
                ],

                  "event": {

                  },
                  "event_ts": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "format": "int64",
                    "description": "A timestamp at which the event occurred."

                        "description": "The meeting host's account ID."

                          "participant"

                            "description": "The meeting's universally unique identifier (UUID). Each meeting instance generates a meeting UUID."

                            "type": "object",
                            "description": "Information about the meeting participant.",
                            "required": [
                              "participant_id",
                              "data"
                            ],

                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The participant's meeting user ID. This value is assigned to a participant upon joining a meeting and is only valid for the duration of the meeting."

See [Email address display rules](https://marketplace.zoom.us/docs/api-reference/using-zoom-apis#email-address) for details."

    "phone.call_qos": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "phone"
        ],
        "operationId": "phone.call_qos",
        "requestBody": {
          "description": "# phone.call_qos\n\nThe **Phone call's quality of service (QoS)** event triggers every few seconds. When the call is on-going, the call's quality of service data is then collected and sent via this event.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for more information.\n* **Event Subscriptions** must be enabled for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build) with the following configurations:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Phone call's quality of service (QoS)** subscription enabled under the **QSS** event.\n\n\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `phone:read:admin`,`phone:write:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `phone:read:call_qos:master`,`phone:read:call_qos:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `phone.call_qos`\n",
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "object",
                "required": [
                  "event",
                  "event_ts",
                  "payload"
                ],
                "properties": {
                  "event": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "enum": [
                      "phone.call_qos"
                    ],
                    "description": "Name of the event."
                  },
                  "event_ts": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "format": "int64",
                    "description": "Timestamp when the event occurred, in milliseconds since epoch. The value of this field is returned in long (int64) format."
                  },
                  "payload": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "required": [
                      "account_id",
                      "object"
                    ],
                    "properties": {
                      "account_id": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "The Account ID of the owner."
                      },
                      "object": {
                        "type": "object",
                        "required": [
                          "call_id",
                          "call_start_time",
                          "call_qos"
                        ],
                        "properties": {
                          "call_id": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The call ID."
                          },
                          "call_start_time": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "format": "date-time",
                            "description": "The date and time when the call started."
                          },
                          "call_end_time": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "format": "date-time",
                            "description": "The date and time when the call ended. Only shows up if the call ended."
                          },
                          "call_qos": {
                            "type": "object",
                            "description": "The call quality of service (QoS)",
                            "required": [
                              "type",
                              "id",
                              "qos"
                            ],
                            "properties": {
                              "type": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The type: caller or callee."
                              },
                              "id": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The caller or callee's ID."
                              },
                              "user_email": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The caller or callee's email address."
                              },
                              "qos": {
                                "type": "object",
                                "description": "The quality of service (QoS) data.",
                                "required": [
                                  "date_time",
                                  "type",
                                  "details"
                                ],
                                "properties": {
                                  "date_time": {
                                    "type": "string",
                                    "format": "date-time",
                                    "description": "The date and time when the QoS data was received."
                                  },
                                  "type": {
                                    "type": "string",
                                    "description": "The QoS type: sending or receiving."
                                  },
                                  "details": {
                                    "type": "object",
                                    "description": "The quality of service (QoS) details.",
                                    "required": [
                                      "bitrate",
                                      "avg_loss",
                                      "max_loss",
                                      "jitter",
                                      "network_delay",
                                      "mos"
                                    ],
                                    "properties": {
                                      "bitrate": {
                                        "type": "string",
                                        "description": "The bits per second transmitted along a digital network, in Kbsp."
                                      },
                                      "avg_loss": {
                                        "type": "string",
                                        "description": "The average amount of packet loss. For example, the percentage of packets that failed to arrive at their destination."
                                      },
                                      "max_loss": {
                                        "type": "string",
                                        "description": "The maximum amount of packet loss. For example, the maximum percentage of packets that failed to arrive at their destination."
                                      },
                                      "jitter": {
                                        "type": "string",
                                        "description": "The variation in the delay of received packets, in milliseconds."
                                      },
                                      "network_delay": {
                                        "type": "string",
                                        "description": "The amount of time, in milliseconds, that it takes for a Voice Over IP (VoIP) packet to travel from one point to another."
                                      },
                                      "mos": {
                                        "type": "string",
                                        "description": "The Mean Opinion Score (MOS). This measures voice quality on a scale of 1 to 5. A score above or equal to 3.5 means good quality, while below 3.5 means poor quality."
                                      },
                                      "network": {
                                        "type": "string",
                                        "description": "The type of networks such as LAN, WiFi, VPN etc"
                                      }
                                    }
                                  }
                                }
                              }
                            }
                          }
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              },
              "examples": {
                "json-example": {
                  "summary": "JSON example",
                  "value": "{\n  \"event\": \"phone.call_qos\",\n  \"event_ts\": 1626759486127,\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"account_id\": \"2TP-coFVSnmyvYZogk8gAg\",\n    \"object\": {\n      \"call_id\": \"6971668082545971778\",\n      \"call_start_time\": \"2021-06-09T05:42:34Z\",\n      \"call_end_time\": \"2021-06-09T05:43:02Z\",\n      \"call_qos\": {\n        \"type\": \"caller\",\n        \"id\": \"KLN56y2cSzu0pWxUSec4RQ\",\n        \"user_email\": \"hello.test@gmail.com\",\n        \"qos\": {\n          \"date_time\": \"2021-04-26T05:26:00Z\",\n          \"type\": \"sending\",\n          \"details\": {\n            \"bitrate\": \"6\",\n            \"avg_loss\": \"0.0\",\n            \"max_loss\": \"0.0\",\n            \"jitter\": \"8\",\n            \"network_delay\": \"23\",\n            \"mos\": \"4.5\",\n            \"network\": \"LAN\"\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "content": {
              "application/json": {

                    "event",

                            },
                            "call_end_time": {

                            },
                            "call_qos": {
                              "type": "object",
                              "description": "The call quality of service (QoS)",
                              "required": [
                                "type",
                                "id",
                                "qos"
                              ],
                              "properties": {
                                "type": {
                                  "type": "string",
                                  "description": "The type: caller or callee."
                                },
                                "id": {
                                  "type": "string",
                                  "description": "The caller or callee's ID."
                                },
                                "user_email": {
                                  "type": "string",
                                  "description": "The caller or callee's email address."
                                },
                                "qos": {
                                  "type": "object",
                                  "description": "The quality of service (QoS) data.",
                                  "required": [

    "session.user_data": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "session"
        ],
        "operationId": "session.user_data",
        "requestBody": {
          "description": "# session.user_data\n\nThe **Session User Data** event triggers when users in a session make setting changes. For example, when a user enables their camera, an event notification is triggered during the session. When you subscribe to this event, you will receive multiple events in one session for each user.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for more information.\n* Enable **Event Subscriptions** for your Video SDK [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build) with:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Session user Data** subscription enabled under the **QSS** event.\n\n\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard_meetings:read:admin`,`dashboard:read:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**Event type**: `session.user_data`\n",
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "required": [
                  "event",
                  "event_ts",
                  "payload"
                ],
                "properties": {
                  "event": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "description": "The event's name."
                  },
                  "event_ts": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "format": "int64",
                    "description": "A timestamp when the event occurred."
                  },
                  "payload": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "required": [
                      "account_id",
                      "object"
                    ],
                    "properties": {
                      "account_id": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "The Video SDK account ID."
                      },
                      "object": {
                        "type": "object",
                        "description": "Information about the session.",
                        "required": [
                          "session_id",
                          "session_name",
                          "user"
                        ],
                        "properties": {
                          "session_id": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Unique session identifier. Each instance of the session will have its own session_id."
                          },
                          "session_name": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Session name."
                          },
                          "session_key": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The Video SDK custom session ID."
                          },
                          "user": {
                            "type": "object",
                            "description": "Information about the session user.",
                            "required": [
                              "id",
                              "data",
                              "is_original_host"
                            ],
                            "properties": {
                              "id": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The user's unique ID. This value is assigned to the user upon joining a session and is only valid for that session."
                              },
                              "name": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The user's username."
                              },
                              "user_key": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "Another identifier for the user. Can be a number or characters."
                              },
                              "is_original_host": {
                                "type": "boolean",
                                "description": "Whether the current user is the original host of this session."
                              },
                              "data": {
                                "type": "array",
                                "description": "The user's data information.",
                                "items": {
                                  "type": "object",
                                  "properties": {
                                    "device": {
                                      "type": "string",
                                      "description": "The type of device the user used to join the session. \n* Phone - The user joined via PSTN. \n* H.323/SIP - The user joined via an H.323 or SIP device. \n* Windows - The user joined via VoIP using a Windows device. \n* Mac - The user joined via VoIP using a macOS device. \n* iOS - The user joined via VoIP using an iOS device. \n* Android - The user joined via VoIP using an Android device.",
                                      "enum": [
                                        "Phone",
                                        "H.323/SIP",
                                        "Windows",
                                        "Mac",
                                        "iOS",
                                        "Android"
                                      ]
                                    },
                                    "location": {
                                      "type": "string",
                                      "description": "The user's location."
                                    },
                                    "network_type": {
                                      "type": "string",
                                      "description": "The user's network type. \n\n* Wired \n* Wifi \n* PPP - Point-to-Point. \n* Cellular - 3G, 4G, and 5G cellular. \n* Others - An unknown device.",
                                      "enum": [
                                        "Wired",
                                        "Wifi",
                                        "PPP",
                                        "Cellular",
                                        "Others"
                                      ]
                                    },
                                    "microphone": {
                                      "type": "string",
                                      "description": "The type of microphone that the user used during the session."
                                    },

The event collects and sends the participants' meeting data.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for more information.\n* **Event Subscriptions** must be enabled for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build) with the following configurations:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Meeting Participant Data Summary** subscription enabled under the **QSS** event.\n\n\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard_meetings:read:admin`,`dashboard:read:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `qss:read:meeting_participant_data:master`,`qss:read:meeting_participant_data:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `meeting.participant_data_summary`\n",

        "requestBody": {
          "description": "# meeting.participant_qos_summary\n\nThe **Meeting Participant QoS Summary** event triggers when a participant leaves a meeting. The meeting participants' QoS data is then collected and sent via this event.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for more information.\n* **Event Subscriptions** must be enabled for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build) with the following configurations:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Meeting Participant QoS Summary** subscription enabled under the **QSS** event.\n\n\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard_meetings:read:admin`,`dashboard:read:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard:read:meeting_participant_qos:master`,`dashboard:read:meeting_participant_qos:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `meeting.participant_qos_summary`\n",

                "type": "object",

                  "event",

                    "type": "string",

    "meeting.participant_qos": {

        "operationId": "meeting.participant_qos",
        "requestBody": {
          "description": "# meeting.participant_qos\n\nWhen participants are in a meeting, the **Meeting Participant QoS** event collects performance data every 6 seconds, aggregates approximately 10 data points into one record every minute, and sends it.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for more information.\n* **Event Subscriptions** must be enabled for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build) with the following configurations:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Meeting Participant QoS** subscription enabled under the **QSS** event.\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard_meetings:read:admin`,`dashboard:read:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard:read:meeting_participant_qos:master`,`dashboard:read:meeting_participant_qos:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `meeting.participant_qos`\n",

              "schema": {
                "required": [
                  "event",
                  "event_ts",
                  "payload"

                    "description": "The name of the event."
                  },

                    "type": "integer",
                    "format": "int64",

                      "object"

                        "description": "The meeting host's account ID."
                      },

                        "description": "Information about the meeting.",

                          "uuid",
                          "participant"
                        ],

                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The meeting's universally unique identifier (UUID). Each meeting instance generates a meeting UUID."
                          },

                            "type": "object",
                            "description": "Information about the meeting participant.",
                            "required": [
                              "user_id",
                              "qos"
                            ],

                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The participant's meeting user ID. This value is assigned to a participant upon joining a meeting and is only valid for the duration of the meeting."

                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The participant's universally unique identifier (UUID). Returns an empty value for external users."

If the participant is not part of the host's account, this returns an empty string value, with some exceptions.                                           "enum": [

                                            "fair",
                                            "serious",
                                            "critical"
                                          ]
                                        },
                                        "quality": {

                                          "enum": [

                                            "fair",
                                            "good",

These levels are rough estimates of CPU usage: normal (~20%), fair (~50%), serious (~80%), and critical (~100%).",

                                            "description": "Unit of the wireless network's received signal strength indicator (RSSI).",
                                            "example": "dBm"

    "webinar.participant_qos": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "webinar"
        ],
        "operationId": "webinar.participant_qos",
        "requestBody": {
          "description": "# webinar.participant_qos\n\nWhen participants are in a webinar, the **Webinar Participant QoS** event collects performance metrics every 6 seconds. Zoom aggregates roughly 10 data into a single record every minute, then sends it to your endpoint.\n\n## Prerequisites\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for details.\n* **Event Subscriptions** must be enabled for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build), including:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Webinar Participant QoS** event enabled under the **QSS** event category.\n\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard_webinars:read:admin`,`dashboard:read:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard:read:webinar_participant_qos:master`,`dashboard:read:webinar_participant_qos:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `webinar.participant_qos`\n",
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "required": [
                  "event",
                  "event_ts",
                  "payload"
                ],
                "properties": {
                  "event": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "description": "The event's name."
                  },
                  "event_ts": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "format": "int64",
                    "description": "Timestamp in milliseconds since epoch when the event occurred. The value is returned in long (int64) format."
                  },
                  "payload": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "required": [
                      "account_id",
                      "object"
                    ],
                    "properties": {
                      "account_id": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "The Account ID associated with the event."
                      },
                      "object": {
                        "type": "object",
                        "description": "Meeting object.",
                        "required": [
                          "uuid",
                          "participant"
                        ],
                        "properties": {
                          "uuid": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The meeting's universally unique identifier (UUID)."
                          },
                          "participant": {
                            "type": "object",
                            "description": "Participant object.",
                            "required": [
                              "user_id",
                              "qos"
                            ],
                            "properties": {
                              "user_id": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The participant's unique identifier."
                              },
                              "participant_user_id": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The participant's universally unique identifier (UUID). Returns an empty value for external users."
                              },
                              "email": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "format": "email",
                                "description": "The participant's email address. This response only returns a value if the participant joined the meeting by logging into Zoom. If the participant is not part of the host's account, this returns an empty string value, with some exceptions. See [Email address display rules](/docs/api/using-zoom-apis/#email-address-display-rules) for details."
                              },
                              "qos": {
                                "type": "array",
                                "description": "An array of Quality of Service (QoS) data.",
                                "items": {
                                  "type": "object",
                                  "description": "Quality of Service (QoS) items.",
                                  "required": [
                                    "date_time",
                                    "type",
                                    "details"
                                  ],
                                  "properties": {
                                    "date_time": {
                                      "type": "string",
                                      "description": "The timestamp for when the participant left."
                                    },
                                    "type": {
                                      "type": "string",
                                      "description": "Quality of Service (QoS) type.",
                                      "enum": [
                                        "audio_input",
                                        "audio_output",
                                        "video_input",
                                        "video_output",
                                        "as_input",
                                        "as_output",
                                        "cpu_usage",

          "description": "# webinar.participant_qos_summary\n\nThe **Webinar Participant QoS Summary** event triggers each time a participant leaves a webinar. The collected QoS metrics for that participant are then sent via this event.\n\n## Prerequisites\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for details.\n* **Event Subscriptions** must be enabled for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build), including:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Webinar Participant QoS Summary** event enabled under the **QSS** event category.\n\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard_webinars:read:admin`,`dashboard:read:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard:read:webinar_participant_qos:master`,`dashboard:read:webinar_participant_qos:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `webinar.participant_qos_summary`\n",

        "requestBody": {
          "description": "# meeting.participant_data\n\nThe **Meeting Participant Data** event triggers when participants in a meeting make setting changes. For example, when a participant enables their camera, there will be an event notification triggered during the meeting. When you subscribe to this event, you will receive multiple events in one meeting for each participant.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for more information.\n* **Event Subscriptions** must be enabled for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build) with the following configurations:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Meeting Participant Data** subscription enabled under the **QSS** event.\n\n\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard_meetings:read:admin`,`dashboard:read:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `qss:read:meeting_participant_data:master`,`qss:read:meeting_participant_data:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `meeting.participant_data`\n",

            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "required": [
                  "event",
                  "event_ts",
                  "payload"
                ],

                  "event": {

                  },
                  "event_ts": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "format": "int64",
                    "description": "A timestamp at which the event occurred."

                        "description": "The meeting host's account ID."

                          "participant"

                            "description": "The meeting's universally unique identifier (UUID). Each meeting instance generates a meeting UUID."

                            "type": "object",
                            "description": "Information about the meeting participant.",
                            "required": [
                              "participant_id",
                              "data"
                            ],

                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The participant's meeting user ID. This value is assigned to a participant upon joining a meeting and is only valid for the duration of the meeting."

See [Email address display rules](https://marketplace.zoom.us/docs/api-reference/using-zoom-apis#email-address) for details."

    "phone.call_qos": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "phone"
        ],
        "operationId": "phone.call_qos",
        "requestBody": {
          "description": "# phone.call_qos\n\nThe **Phone call's quality of service (QoS)** event triggers every few seconds. When the call is on-going, the call's quality of service data is then collected and sent via this event.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for more information.\n* **Event Subscriptions** must be enabled for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build) with the following configurations:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Phone call's quality of service (QoS)** subscription enabled under the **QSS** event.\n\n\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `phone:read:admin`,`phone:write:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `phone:read:call_qos:master`,`phone:read:call_qos:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `phone.call_qos`\n",
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "object",
                "required": [
                  "event",
                  "event_ts",
                  "payload"
                ],
                "properties": {
                  "event": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "enum": [
                      "phone.call_qos"
                    ],
                    "description": "Name of the event."
                  },
                  "event_ts": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "format": "int64",
                    "description": "Timestamp when the event occurred, in milliseconds since epoch. The value of this field is returned in long (int64) format."
                  },
                  "payload": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "required": [
                      "account_id",
                      "object"
                    ],
                    "properties": {
                      "account_id": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "The Account ID of the owner."
                      },
                      "object": {
                        "type": "object",
                        "required": [
                          "call_id",
                          "call_start_time",
                          "call_qos"
                        ],
                        "properties": {
                          "call_id": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The call ID."
                          },
                          "call_start_time": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "format": "date-time",
                            "description": "The date and time when the call started."
                          },
                          "call_end_time": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "format": "date-time",
                            "description": "The date and time when the call ended. Only shows up if the call ended."
                          },
                          "call_qos": {
                            "type": "object",
                            "description": "The call quality of service (QoS)",
                            "required": [
                              "type",
                              "id",
                              "qos"
                            ],
                            "properties": {
                              "type": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The type: caller or callee."
                              },
                              "id": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The caller or callee's ID."
                              },
                              "user_email": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The caller or callee's email address."
                              },
                              "qos": {
                                "type": "object",
                                "description": "The quality of service (QoS) data.",
                                "required": [
                                  "date_time",
                                  "type",
                                  "details"
                                ],
                                "properties": {
                                  "date_time": {
                                    "type": "string",
                                    "format": "date-time",
                                    "description": "The date and time when the QoS data was received."
                                  },
                                  "type": {
                                    "type": "string",
                                    "description": "The QoS type: sending or receiving."
                                  },
                                  "details": {
                                    "type": "object",
                                    "description": "The quality of service (QoS) details.",
                                    "required": [
                                      "bitrate",
                                      "avg_loss",
                                      "max_loss",
                                      "jitter",
                                      "network_delay",
                                      "mos"
                                    ],
                                    "properties": {
                                      "bitrate": {
                                        "type": "string",
                                        "description": "The bits per second transmitted along a digital network, in Kbsp."
                                      },
                                      "avg_loss": {
                                        "type": "string",
                                        "description": "The average amount of packet loss. For example, the percentage of packets that failed to arrive at their destination."
                                      },
                                      "max_loss": {
                                        "type": "string",
                                        "description": "The maximum amount of packet loss. For example, the maximum percentage of packets that failed to arrive at their destination."
                                      },
                                      "jitter": {
                                        "type": "string",
                                        "description": "The variation in the delay of received packets, in milliseconds."
                                      },
                                      "network_delay": {
                                        "type": "string",
                                        "description": "The amount of time, in milliseconds, that it takes for a Voice Over IP (VoIP) packet to travel from one point to another."
                                      },
                                      "mos": {
                                        "type": "string",
                                        "description": "The Mean Opinion Score (MOS). This measures voice quality on a scale of 1 to 5. A score above or equal to 3.5 means good quality, while below 3.5 means poor quality."
                                      },
                                      "network": {
                                        "type": "string",
                                        "description": "The type of networks such as LAN, WiFi, VPN etc"
                                      }
                                    }
                                  }
                                }
                              }
                            }
                          }
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              },
              "examples": {
                "json-example": {
                  "summary": "JSON example",
                  "value": "{\n  \"event\": \"phone.call_qos\",\n  \"event_ts\": 1626759486127,\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"account_id\": \"2TP-coFVSnmyvYZogk8gAg\",\n    \"object\": {\n      \"call_id\": \"6971668082545971778\",\n      \"call_start_time\": \"2021-06-09T05:42:34Z\",\n      \"call_end_time\": \"2021-06-09T05:43:02Z\",\n      \"call_qos\": {\n        \"type\": \"caller\",\n        \"id\": \"KLN56y2cSzu0pWxUSec4RQ\",\n        \"user_email\": \"hello.test@gmail.com\",\n        \"qos\": {\n          \"date_time\": \"2021-04-26T05:26:00Z\",\n          \"type\": \"sending\",\n          \"details\": {\n            \"bitrate\": \"6\",\n            \"avg_loss\": \"0.0\",\n            \"max_loss\": \"0.0\",\n            \"jitter\": \"8\",\n            \"network_delay\": \"23\",\n            \"mos\": \"4.5\",\n            \"network\": \"LAN\"\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "content": {
              "application/json": {

                    "event",

                            },
                            "call_end_time": {

                            },
                            "call_qos": {
                              "type": "object",
                              "description": "The call quality of service (QoS)",
                              "required": [
                                "type",
                                "id",
                                "qos"
                              ],
                              "properties": {
                                "type": {
                                  "type": "string",
                                  "description": "The type: caller or callee."
                                },
                                "id": {
                                  "type": "string",
                                  "description": "The caller or callee's ID."
                                },
                                "user_email": {
                                  "type": "string",
                                  "description": "The caller or callee's email address."
                                },
                                "qos": {
                                  "type": "object",
                                  "description": "The quality of service (QoS) data.",
                                  "required": [

    "session.user_data": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "session"
        ],
        "operationId": "session.user_data",
        "requestBody": {
          "description": "# session.user_data\n\nThe **Session User Data** event triggers when users in a session make setting changes. For example, when a user enables their camera, an event notification is triggered during the session. When you subscribe to this event, you will receive multiple events in one session for each user.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for more information.\n* Enable **Event Subscriptions** for your Video SDK [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build) with:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Session user Data** subscription enabled under the **QSS** event.\n\n\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard_meetings:read:admin`,`dashboard:read:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**Event type**: `session.user_data`\n",
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "required": [
                  "event",
                  "event_ts",
                  "payload"
                ],
                "properties": {
                  "event": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "description": "The event's name."
                  },
                  "event_ts": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "format": "int64",
                    "description": "A timestamp when the event occurred."
                  },
                  "payload": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "required": [
                      "account_id",
                      "object"
                    ],
                    "properties": {
                      "account_id": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "The Video SDK account ID."
                      },
                      "object": {
                        "type": "object",
                        "description": "Information about the session.",
                        "required": [
                          "session_id",
                          "session_name",
                          "user"
                        ],
                        "properties": {
                          "session_id": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Unique session identifier. Each instance of the session will have its own session_id."
                          },
                          "session_name": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Session name."
                          },
                          "session_key": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The Video SDK custom session ID."
                          },
                          "user": {
                            "type": "object",
                            "description": "Information about the session user.",
                            "required": [
                              "id",
                              "data",
                              "is_original_host"
                            ],
                            "properties": {
                              "id": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The user's unique ID. This value is assigned to the user upon joining a session and is only valid for that session."
                              },
                              "name": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "The user's username."
                              },
                              "user_key": {
                                "type": "string",
                                "description": "Another identifier for the user. Can be a number or characters."
                              },
                              "is_original_host": {
                                "type": "boolean",
                                "description": "Whether the current user is the original host of this session."
                              },
                              "data": {
                                "type": "array",
                                "description": "The user's data information.",
                                "items": {
                                  "type": "object",
                                  "properties": {
                                    "device": {
                                      "type": "string",
                                      "description": "The type of device the user used to join the session. \n* Phone - The user joined via PSTN. \n* H.323/SIP - The user joined via an H.323 or SIP device. \n* Windows - The user joined via VoIP using a Windows device. \n* Mac - The user joined via VoIP using a macOS device. \n* iOS - The user joined via VoIP using an iOS device. \n* Android - The user joined via VoIP using an Android device.",
                                      "enum": [
                                        "Phone",
                                        "H.323/SIP",
                                        "Windows",
                                        "Mac",
                                        "iOS",
                                        "Android"
                                      ]
                                    },
                                    "location": {
                                      "type": "string",
                                      "description": "The user's location."
                                    },
                                    "network_type": {
                                      "type": "string",
                                      "description": "The user's network type. \n\n* Wired \n* Wifi \n* PPP - Point-to-Point. \n* Cellular - 3G, 4G, and 5G cellular. \n* Others - An unknown device.",
                                      "enum": [
                                        "Wired",
                                        "Wifi",
                                        "PPP",
                                        "Cellular",
                                        "Others"
                                      ]
                                    },
                                    "microphone": {
                                      "type": "string",
                                      "description": "The type of microphone that the user used during the session."
                                    },

The event collects and sends the participants' meeting data.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for more information.\n* **Event Subscriptions** must be enabled for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build) with the following configurations:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Meeting Participant Data Summary** subscription enabled under the **QSS** event.\n\n\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard_meetings:read:admin`,`dashboard:read:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `qss:read:meeting_participant_data:master`,`qss:read:meeting_participant_data:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `meeting.participant_data_summary`\n",

        "requestBody": {
          "description": "# meeting.participant_qos_summary\n\nThe **Meeting Participant QoS Summary** event triggers when a participant leaves a meeting. The meeting participants' QoS data is then collected and sent via this event.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n* A **Quality of Service Subscription** plan. [Contact Zoom Sales](https://explore.zoom.us/en/contactsales/) for more information.\n* **Event Subscriptions** must be enabled for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build) with the following configurations:\n  * A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL**.\n  * The **Meeting Participant QoS Summary** subscription enabled under the **QSS** event.\n\n\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard_meetings:read:admin`,`dashboard:read:admin`,`dashboard:master`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `dashboard:read:meeting_participant_qos:master`,`dashboard:read:meeting_participant_qos:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `meeting.participant_qos_summary`\n",

                "type": "object",

                  "event",

                    "type": "string",
